Nine suspects linked to fraudulent drivers licences issued in Carnarvon, Northern Cape have been granted bail for R3 000 each and the case has been postponed to 17 April. The suspects aged between 26 and 46 appeared briefly at the Carnarvon Magistrate Court on Thursday to face charges of fraud and corruption. The Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation unit arrested the suspects in various places in the Western Cape on Monday and Tuesday. During the arrest, police obtained drivers licences without being subjected to mandatory tests and eight were seized. -TNA Reporter  